        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 4:22PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Penrose, or 22 miles west of Pueblo, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beulah, Wetmore, Florence, and Penrose.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
